---
import PolicyBlock from '../PolicyBlock.astro';
import PolicySection from '../PolicySection.astro';
---

<PolicyBlock
  id="privacy-hablame"
  title="TalkToMe"
  badgeLabel="Privacy Policy"
  extraBadge="In Development"
  updated="July 5, 2026"
>
  <PolicySection heading="Overview">
    <p>
      Ball Studios ("we", "our") operates the mobile application
      <strong>TalkToMe</strong>.
      This document describes how data is collected and used when you use the App.
      TalkToMe is a conversational companion app: you chat with a roster of
      AI-driven characters, some styled as specialists (a psychologist,
      nutritionist, personal coach, language tutor, and others), and play
      built-in mini-games that reward you with credits.
    </p>
  </PolicySection>

  <PolicySection heading="Data we collect">
    <p>
      Every install is identified by an anonymous Firebase account — no name,
      email, or phone number is required to use the App. The following data is
      stored on our servers, tied to that anonymous identifier:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Your credit balance and daily bonus status</li>
      <li>Your conversation history with each AI character</li>
    </ul>
    <p style="margin-top:0.75rem">
      If you choose the optional "continue with email" flow, the email address
      and display name you enter are stored <strong>only locally on your
      device</strong> to personalize how the App addresses you — they are not
      transmitted to or stored on our servers. Your account identity remains the
      same anonymous Firebase identifier either way. Preferences, game scores,
      and character customization are also stored only on your device.
    </p>
  </PolicySection>

  <PolicySection heading="AI companions">
    <p>
      The App's core feature is conversing with AI-generated characters. In
      compliance with the <strong>EU AI Act</strong> (in force August 2026), we
      inform you that these characters are powered by an artificial intelligence
      system, not a human — this is disclosed the first time you open the App.
    </p>
    <p style="margin-top:0.75rem">
      When you send a message, it is forwarded from a secure backend proxy
      (hosted on Render) to <strong>DeepSeek</strong> (operated by DeepSeek AI,
      People's Republic of China), which generates the reply. Unlike a
      statistics-only integration, the message content itself — what you type in
      the chat — is sent to DeepSeek to produce a relevant response.
    </p>
    <p style="margin-top:0.75rem">
      <strong>International transfer notice:</strong> DeepSeek is based in China,
      a country without an EU adequacy decision. By using the App, you
      acknowledge that your messages will be transferred to and processed in
      China under DeepSeek's terms. Avoid sending information in the chat that
      you would not want processed by a third party (ID documents, passwords,
      financial details, etc.).
    </p>
    <p style="margin-top:0.75rem">
      DeepSeek's data practices are governed by
      <a href="https://www.deepseek.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">DeepSeek's Privacy Policy</a>.
    </p>
  </PolicySection>

  <PolicySection heading="Advertising">
    <p>
      The App uses <strong>Google AdMob</strong> to display banner ads in the
      mini-games. AdMob may collect data to serve personalized ads, including:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Device identifiers (Advertising ID)</li>
      <li>IP address and approximate location</li>
      <li>Interaction data with displayed ads</li>
      <li>App usage information</li>
    </ul>
    <p style="margin-top:0.75rem">
      Users in the <strong>EEA and UK</strong> are shown a consent dialog powered
      by <strong>Google's User Messaging Platform (UMP)</strong> before
      personalized ads are served. You may withdraw consent at any time through
      your device settings under <em>Privacy → Ads</em>. Google's data practices
      are governed by
      <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google's Privacy Policy</a>.
    </p>
  </PolicySection>

  <PolicySection heading="Backup & data portability">
    <p>
      You can export an encrypted backup of your conversations and progress at any
      time from the App's profile screen, protected by a password you choose. That
      password is the only way to decrypt the file — Ball Studios cannot recover it
      for you — and safeguarding it is your responsibility. The same screen lets you
      restore a previously exported backup.
    </p>
  </PolicySection>

  <PolicySection heading="Children's privacy">
    <p>
      The App is not directed at children under 13. We do not knowingly collect
      personal data from children. If you believe a child has provided personal
      information, contact us and we will delete it promptly.
    </p>
  </PolicySection>

  <PolicySection heading="Data deletion">
    <p>
      Because accounts are anonymous, uninstalling the App removes it from your
      device but does not automatically delete the associated server-side data —
      we have no way to link that data back to you once you lose access to the
      anonymous identifier stored on your device. If you would like your
      conversation history and credits deleted, contact us
      <strong>before uninstalling</strong> so we can locate and remove your record,
      or use the in-App account deletion option if available in a future update.
    </p>
  </PolicySection>

  <PolicySection heading="Lawful basis (EEA & UK)">
    <p>Where we process personal data, the lawful basis under GDPR is:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Contract</strong> — storing your credits and conversation
          history to provide the core service</li>
      <li><strong>Consent</strong> — the AI-processing and data-storage notice
          shown and accepted the first time you open the App; personalized
          advertising via AdMob (EEA/UK)</li>
      <li><strong>Legitimate interest</strong> — non-personalized ads; anonymous
          usage analytics to improve the App</li>
    </ul>
  </PolicySection>

  <PolicySection heading="Your rights">
    <p>If you are in the EEA, UK, or California, you have the following rights:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Access</strong> — request a copy of personal data we hold about you</li>
      <li><strong>Erasure</strong> — request deletion of your conversation history and credits</li>
      <li><strong>Portability</strong> — export your conversations and progress via the App's backup feature</li>
      <li><strong>Objection</strong> — object to processing based on legitimate interest</li>
      <li><strong>Opt-out of data sharing</strong> (California) — opt out of ad data sharing via device settings</li>
    </ul>
    <p style="margin-top:0.75rem">
      To exercise these rights, contact us at
<a
        class="about-cta"
        href="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLScMVe3zWAij_TeCoYU03qG2ggQVVJMWYmuq8J1hfybdmcohpg/viewform"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
        aria-label="Open Ball Studios questionnaire"
      >
        Contact
      </a>      We will respond within 30 days.
    </p>
  </PolicySection>

  <PolicySection heading="Data retention">
    <p>
      Conversation history and credits persist on our servers until you request
      deletion or we discontinue the App. Locally stored preferences and game
      progress persist until you uninstall the App. AdMob data retention is governed
      by <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google's Privacy Policy</a>,
      and DeepSeek's by its own
      <a href="https://www.deepseek.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Privacy Policy</a>.
    </p>
  </PolicySection>

  <PolicySection heading="Contact">
    <p>
      Questions about this policy:
      <a
        class="about-cta"
        href="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLScMVe3zWAij_TeCoYU03qG2ggQVVJMWYmuq8J1hfybdmcohpg/viewform"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
        aria-label="Open Ball Studios questionnaire"
      >
        Contact
      </a>
    </p>
  </PolicySection>
</PolicyBlock>
